Wash and dry produce. Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked from stems) from stems; finely chop leaves. Trim and halve @chili pepper{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise, removing ribs and seeds for less heat); mince chili.

In a #large bowl{}, combine cilantro, half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), @cumin{1%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and as much chili as you like. (You'll use the rest of the cumin and garlic powder later.) Whisk in @olive oil{4%tablespoon} (8 TBSP for 4). Taste and season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Chop @baby lettuce{1}(chopped into bite-size pieces). Halve, pit, peel, and dice @avocado{1}(halved, pitted, peeled, and diced). Dice @tomato{1}(diced). Peel, halve, and thinly slice half @red onion{1}(peeled, halved, and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4 servings).

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season with remaining @cumin{1%teaspoon}, remaining @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in 1 TBSP dressing (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} and chop into bite-size pieces if necessary. Set aside.

To bowl with dressing, toss together lettuce, avocado, tomato, and sliced onion until coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Stir in half the chicken and half the @pepper jack cheese{1/4%cup}.

Divide salad between bowls. Top with remaining chicken and remaining pepper jack. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.